The paper focuses on exploring the interaction of update propagation, coherence protocols, and memory consistency models for graph workloads on integrated GPU-CPU systems. This falls under the categories of computer architecture (cs.AR), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), performance (cs.PF), and software engineering (cs.SE).
